LAGOS – One of the cardinal focus of Falusi Adedayo Omolade Foundation (FAO Foundation) launched by Adedayo Omolade Falusi is providing formal education to underprivileged children in Nigeria. The foundation has been touching the lives of Nigerians since it was founded in 2019. Adedayo Falusi has made several donations to orphanages and centres for the less privileged in Lagos, Ondo and Delta States. The philanthropist has on several occasions emphasised that the core of his foundation is to “empower” men, women, as well as children in the area of education combined with technology. -Advertisement- The generous and kind Adedayo Falusi has taken the challenge of indigent schoolchildren head-on in Nigeria. The charitable businessman believes that when a platform is provided, the children can go on to fulfill their great destinies and be world changers, movers and shakers. “I want you all to become empowered and gradually, we are achieving that milestone. When you are empowered, you can easily do things on your own abilities, care for your kids, have good shelter, feed well and gain the confidence to fulfil your potentials,” Adedayo Falusi mentioned at a recent event. The FAO foundation visioner regularly pays school fess for poor children and he is not just ensuring that they have access to education, he is exposing them early to technology. “We also facilitate the progress of growing kids, particularly kids that circumstances of life robbed from exposure to the right education. We are always striving to bring out potentials in them especially in field of Tech as one of the fastest growing industry”, Adedayo Falusi stated. Continuing, Adedayo Falusi said, “The foundation also embarked on consistent feeding of the children in various communities, in order to make sure they are sound mentally and psychologically to excel in their studies.”